The article discusses a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump in response to the shooting in Sutherland Springs, Texas, which occurred on November 5, 2017. The proclamation expresses deep sadness over the incident and offers prayers for healing and comfort to the victims' families and loved ones. As a mark of respect, President Trump orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations, including the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels, until sunset on November 9, 2017. The proclamation also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff at United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad for the same duration. The proclamation is dated November 5, 2017.